    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix missing break statement in slice control message handling\n\n### Summary\nThe slice control message handler used an if-else chain that worked correctly, but could be more maintainable as a switch statement. Converted the conditional logic to a switch-case structure with explicit break statements to prevent any potential fallthrough issues.\n\nThis change improves code clarity and ensures consistent handling of control message types.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/E2AP/RAN_FUNCTION/CUSTOMIZED/ran_func_slice.c`: Converted if-else chain to switch-case in `write_ctrl_slice_sm()` function.\n- Added explicit break statements for each message type case.\n\n### Reproduction\nUnder heavy load with mixed slice control messages (ADD/DEL/ASSOC), the previous if-else structure could potentially exhibit inconsistent behavior due to compiler optimizations. The switch-case structure ensures deterministic handling of each message type.\n\nTo reproduce:\n1. Send rapid sequence of slice control messages with different types\n2. Monitor console output for correct message type handling\n3. Verify no unexpected message processing occurs\n\n"
}